This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with activity recognition using surveillance cameras. The use of attention transfer also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The mention of information capacity and privacy protection suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of high-resolution data and state-of-the-art performance on datasets suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the mention of privacy protection suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
